                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; name of the king (occasionally only
                           the first component rubricated); name of the donor (occasionally only the
                           second component rubricated); incipits (usually first two lines) of major
                           texts; first words of minor texts and structural parts of texts; some of
                           the interlinear musical signs; elements of the punctuation signs;
                           abbreviations; quire numbers (either wholly or only elements of the two
                           horizontal bars above and below the number).
 
 Two groups of
                           lines on the incipit page of Text I.</seg>
